contrary, shown that higelak in beowulf “drapa,” is
the same person as the danish king cochilac, whose fall in a battle with the frank|franke king, is related by gregory of tours. these are slight
defects, but, perhaps, not unworthy of notice; and having suggested them to the attention of the reader, we can very sincerely recommende mr.
wheaton volumes.
